/-!
# Weakly √©tale field extensions

Stacks tag [092P] (`lem:flat-tensor-over-field-imples-algebraic`): if `L / K` is an
extension of fields and the multiplication `L ‚äó[K] L ‚Üí L` is flat (equivalently
`Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L`), then `L` is a separable algebraic extension of `K`.

## Main result

* `Algebra.WeaklyEtale.isSeparable_algebraic_of_isField` ‚Äî
  a weakly √©tale extension between fields is separable algebraic.

## Proof sketch (Stacks 092P)

Let `Œº : L ‚äó[K] L ‚Üí L` denote multiplication; by assumption `Œº` is flat. Because
`L` is a field and `Œº(1 ‚äó a) = a`, the map `Œº` is also surjective, so its kernel
`J` is generated by elements of the form `1 ‚äó a - a ‚äó 1` for `a ‚àà L`. The
flatness of `Œº` (a flat surjection between commutative rings) forces
`J = J¬≤` (cf. `Algebra.WeaklyEtale.formallyUnramified_of_flat`). Combined with
the fact that `L ‚äó[K] L` is reduced (a consequence of weakly-√©tale-over-field
via `Algebra.FormallyUnramified.isReduced_of_field`), one shows that the
diagonal `Spec L ‚Ü™ Spec (L ‚äó[K] L)` is both open and closed.

Pulling back this clopen subscheme along the map `Spec L ‚Üí Spec K[X]` sending
`X` to any `a ‚àà L` produces a non-trivial idempotent of `L[X] ‚âÖ K[X] ‚äó[K] L`
that picks out the point `X = a`. Since `L[X]` is an integral domain and its
only idempotents up to localisation are governed by polynomial factorisations,
this forces `a` to be a root of some polynomial in `K[X]`, hence algebraic
over `K`.

Once `L / K` is algebraic, separability follows: each `K(a)` is finite (hence
`EssFiniteType`) over `K`, and `L ‚äó[K] L ‚Üí L` flat implies the same for
`K(a) ‚äó[K] K(a) ‚Üí K(a)` after restriction. Applying
`Algebra.FormallyUnramified.iff_isSeparable` to each `K(a)` shows every
element is separable, so `L / K` is separable.

Full details: [Stacks 092P](https://stacks.math.columbia.edu/tag/092P).
-/

universe u

open scoped TensorProduct
open Algebra

namespace Algebra.WeaklyEtale

variable (K L : Type u) [Field K] [Field L] [Algebra K L]

/-- The multiplication map `L ‚äó[K] L ‚Üí L` is surjective for fields (in fact, for any
nontrivial `K`-algebra `L` admitting a unit on the right). This is a trivial observation:
`(1 ‚äó x) ‚Ü¶ x`. -/
lemma surjective_lmul'_of_field :
    Function.Surjective (Algebra.TensorProduct.lmul' (R := K) (S := L)) := by
  intro x
  exact ‚ü®1 ‚äó‚Çú x, by simp‚ü©

/-- If `L / K` is weakly √©tale between fields, then `L` is formally unramified over `K`.
This is immediate from the general `Algebra.WeaklyEtale ‚áí Algebra.FormallyUnramified`
instance, restated here for convenience. -/
lemma formallyUnramified_of_isField [Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L] :
    Algebra.FormallyUnramified K L :=
  inferInstance

/-- If `L / K` is weakly √©tale between fields, then `L ‚äó[K] L` is reduced.

This is the special-field version: derived from `Ring.AbsolutelyFlat (L ‚äó[K] L)` via
the TFAE result `Ring.AbsolutelyFlat.tfae` (absolutely flat ‚áí reduced + all primes
maximal). -/
instance isReduced_tensor_self [Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L] :
    IsReduced (L ‚äó[K] L) := by
  haveI : Ring.AbsolutelyFlat (L ‚äó[K] L) := absolutelyFlat_tensor_self K L
  refine isReduced_ofLocalizationMaximal _ fun P hP ‚Ü¶ ?_
  haveI : P.IsPrime := hP.isPrime
  haveI hfld : IsField (Localization.AtPrime P) :=
    Ring.AbsolutelyFlat.isField_of_isLocalization_prime
      (R := L ‚äó[K] L) P (Localization.AtPrime P)
  letI := hfld.toField
  infer_instance

/-- If `L / K` is weakly √©tale between fields and `a ‚àà L`, then the element
`1 ‚äó a - a ‚äó 1 ‚àà L ‚äó[K] L` lies in the kernel of multiplication. -/
lemma sub_mem_ker_lmul' (a : L) :
    (1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a - a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 : L ‚äó[K] L) ‚àà
      RingHom.ker (Algebra.TensorProduct.lmul' (R := K) (S := L)).toRingHom := by
  simp [RingHom.mem_ker]

/-- Helper (iter-020 scaffolding) for the `Œ¥ ‚âÝ 0` substantive case of
`isSeparable_algebraic_of_isField` (Stacks [092P]). Given a weakly √©tale
extension of fields `K ‚Üí L` and `a ‚àà L` with `1 ‚äó a ‚âÝ a ‚äó 1` in `L ‚äó_K L`,
`a` is algebraic over `K`.

Proof strategy (Stacks [092K] route, iter-020 pivot from polyEquivTensor):

1. Form the K-subalgebra `Aa := Algebra.adjoin K {a} ‚äÜ L`.
2. **Descent step (the residual gap)**: show `K ‚Üí Aa` is weakly √©tale.
   This is the field-to-field special case of Stacks 092K (weakly √©tale
   subalgebras). One direct approach: `K ‚Üí L` weakly √©tale + `Aa ‚Üí L` flat
   (automatic since `L` is `Aa`-torsion-free as a field overextension of
   either `K[X]` or a finite field extension `K(a)`); but flat-descent of
   weakly √©tale requires faithful flatness, which fails when `a` is
   transcendental (`K[X] ‚Üí L` is not faithfully flat). The actual descent
   goes via K√§hler differentials / formally unramified directly: the
   inclusion `Aa ‚äó_K Aa ‚Ü™ L ‚äó_K L` is K-flat-injective, and idempotency
   of `ker Œº_L` should restrict to idempotency of `ker Œº_{Aa}` after a
   careful argument inside the subring.
3. From step 2: `Aa ‚äó_K Aa ‚Üí Aa` is flat ‚áí `ker Œº_{Aa}` is idempotent
   (by `Algebra.FormallyEtale.iff_of_surjective` applied to `Œº_{Aa}`).
4. Case-split on `a` transcendental vs algebraic.
   * `a` transcendental: `Aa ‚âÖ K[X]` so `Aa ‚äó_K Aa ‚âÖ K[X, Y]` (domain).
     `ker Œº_{Aa}` is the principal ideal `(X - Y)`. By
     `Ideal.isIdempotentElem_iff_eq_bot_or_top` (which requires the
     domain hypothesis), `(X - Y) = ‚ä•` or `‚ä§`. Both impossible:
     `X - Y ‚âÝ 0` (so `‚âÝ ‚ä•`), and `1 ‚àâ (X - Y)` (so `‚âÝ ‚ä§`).
   * `a` algebraic: done by definition of `IsAlgebraic`.

The residual gap is step 2 (the descent). Once that helper lands (likely
as a new file `Proetale/Mathlib/RingTheory/WeaklyEtale/Subalgebra.lean`),
steps 3‚Äì4 are mechanical. -/
private theorem isAlgebraic_of_isField_aux (a : L) [Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L]
    (_hŒ¥_ne : (1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a - a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 : L ‚äó[K] L) ‚âÝ 0) :
    IsAlgebraic K a := by
  -- Stacks 092K subalgebra descent ‚Äî residual gap. See docstring above for
  -- the full strategy. Implementation deferred to a new infrastructure file
  -- `Proetale/Mathlib/RingTheory/WeaklyEtale/Subalgebra.lean`.
  sorry

/-- (Stacks [092P].) If `L / K` is an extension of fields with `K ‚Üí L` weakly √©tale,
then `L` is a separable algebraic extension of `K`.

This is the key reduction Stacks 092Q (`Algebra.WeaklyEtale.indEtale_of_isField`)
relies on: the local rings of a weakly √©tale `K`-algebra `B` are fields, and applying
this lemma to each shows they are separable algebraic over `K`, which then feeds into
the proof that `B` is itself ind-√©tale.

The proof is the subject of the blueprint section
`lem:flat-tensor-over-field-imples-algebraic` in
`blueprint/src/chapters/more-on-local-structure.tex`. The mathematical strategy is:
flatness of `L ‚äó[K] L ‚Üí L` makes the diagonal clopen in `Spec (L ‚äó[K] L)`; pulling
back via `K[X] ‚Üí L`, `X ‚Ü¶ a` yields a polynomial relation on each `a ‚àà L`. -/
theorem isSeparable_algebraic_of_isField [Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L] :
    Algebra.IsSeparable K L ‚àß Algebra.IsAlgebraic K L := by
  -- Step 1: derive `Algebra.FormallyUnramified K L` from `Algebra.WeaklyEtale K L`.
  haveI : Algebra.FormallyUnramified K L := inferInstance
  -- Step 2 (the heart of 092P): show every `a : L` is algebraic over `K`. The blueprint
  -- argument uses the clopen diagonal `Spec L ‚Ü™ Spec (L ‚äó[K] L)` (which follows from
  -- `L ‚äó L` being absolutely flat, hence reduced + every prime maximal) pulled back
  -- along `K[X] ‚Üí L`, `X ‚Ü¶ a` to land an idempotent in `K[X] ‚äó[K] L ‚âÉ L[X]` whose
  -- support pins down a polynomial relation `p(a) = 0`.
  --
  -- The clopenness ingredients are now available (`absolutelyFlat_tensor_self`,
  -- `isReduced_tensor_self`, `sub_mem_ker_lmul'`), but the precise extraction of
  -- the polynomial relation requires the `polyEquivTensor` (`K[X] ‚âÉ K ‚äó K[X]`,
  -- not yet wired here in the K[X] ‚äó L ‚âÉ L[X] direction) together with a
  -- domain-ness argument on `L[X]`, which has not yet been formalised.
  have h_alg : Algebra.IsAlgebraic K L := by
    refine ‚ü®fun a => ?_‚ü©
    -- For each `a ‚àà L`, the element `Œ¥ := 1 ‚äó a - a ‚äó 1 ‚àà L ‚äó L` lies in `ker (lmul')`,
    -- which is itself an idempotent ideal in the absolutely-flat ring `L ‚äó L`.
    -- The required polynomial relation `p(a) = 0` is extracted by pulling back the
    -- clopen idempotent along the ring map `K[X] ‚Üí L`, `X ‚Ü¶ a`.
    -- See blueprint `lem:flat-tensor-over-field-imples-algebraic`.
    --
    -- Setup: the principal ideal `(Œ¥)` is f.g., hence by `Ring.AbsolutelyFlat`
    -- (= every f.g. ideal is generated by an idempotent ‚Äî `Ideal.isIdempotentElem_iff_of_fg`),
    -- there exists an idempotent `e ‚àà L ‚äó L` with `Ideal.span {Œ¥} = Ideal.span {e}`.
    -- The K-subalgebra `K[e]` is `K[X]/(X¬≤ - X) ‚âÖ K √ó K`. Pulling back via the
    -- L-algebra map `tensorEvalRight K L a : L[X] ‚Üí L ‚äó L` (already defined here)
    -- yields a non-trivial idempotent in `L[X]`. Since `L[X]` is a domain, the only
    -- idempotents are `0` and `1`, so the pullback is constant. This forces a
    -- polynomial relation on `a`.
    --
    -- The detailed extraction (relating the polynomial obtained to a non-trivial
    -- annihilator of `a` over `K`) is a substantial Stacks 092P argument and is
    -- not finished here. The framework variables are set up below.
    -- Abbreviate the diagonal element Œ¥ := 1 ‚äó a - a ‚äó 1.
    set Œ¥ : L ‚äó[K] L := 1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a - a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 with hŒ¥_def
    have hŒ¥ : Œ¥ ‚àà
        RingHom.ker (Algebra.TensorProduct.lmul' (R := K) (S := L)).toRingHom :=
      sub_mem_ker_lmul' K L a
    -- The principal ideal generated by `Œ¥`. It is f.g. (in fact principal).
    let IŒ¥ : Ideal (L ‚äó[K] L) := Ideal.span {Œ¥}
    have hIŒ¥_fg : IŒ¥.FG := ‚ü®{Œ¥}, by simp [IŒ¥]‚ü©
    -- Step (i): `IŒ¥` is idempotent. Proof: the quotient map `q : L‚äóL ‚Üí L‚äóL/IŒ¥`
    -- is surjective; it is also flat because `L‚äóL` is absolutely flat (every module is
    -- flat, in particular `L‚äóL/IŒ¥` is `L‚äóL`-flat). Apply
    -- `exists_eq_mul_of_surjective_flat` to `Œ¥ ‚àà ker q`: there exists `z ‚àà L‚äóL` with
    -- `q(z) = 1` and `z¬∑Œ¥ = 0`. From `q(z) = 1` we get `z - 1 ‚àà IŒ¥`, say
    -- `z - 1 = r¬∑Œ¥`. Combined with `z¬∑Œ¥ = 0` we obtain `Œ¥ + r¬∑Œ¥¬≤ = 0`, i.e.
    -- `Œ¥ ‚àà IŒ¥¬≤`, hence `IŒ¥ ‚äÜ IŒ¥¬≤`.
    have hIŒ¥_idem : IsIdempotentElem IŒ¥ := by
      -- `IŒ¥` is pure because `L‚äóL` is absolutely flat (every quotient is flat).
      haveI : Ring.AbsolutelyFlat (L ‚äó[K] L) := absolutelyFlat_tensor_self K L
      haveI : IŒ¥.Pure := Ring.AbsolutelyFlat.flat IŒ¥
      exact Ideal.isIdempotentElem_of_pure IŒ¥
    -- Step (ii): obtain an idempotent generator `e ‚àà L‚äóL` of `IŒ¥`.
    obtain ‚ü®e, he_idem, he_span‚ü© :=
      (Ideal.isIdempotentElem_iff_of_fg IŒ¥ hIŒ¥_fg).mp hIŒ¥_idem
    -- `Submodule.span R {e} = Ideal.span {e}` definitionally.
    -- Step (iii): `Œº(e) = 0`. Since `e ‚àà IŒ¥ = Ideal.span {Œ¥}`, we have `e = Œ¥¬∑s` for
    -- some `s ‚àà L‚äóL`. Applying `Œº` and using `Œº(Œ¥) = 0`: `Œº(e) = Œº(Œ¥)¬∑Œº(s) = 0`.
    have he_in_IŒ¥ : e ‚àà IŒ¥ := by
      rw [he_span]; exact Submodule.mem_span_singleton_self _
    have hŒºe : (Algebra.TensorProduct.lmul' (R := K) (S := L)).toRingHom e = 0 := by
      -- e ‚àà IŒ¥ ‚äÜ ker Œº.
      have hIŒ¥_subset_ker : IŒ¥ ‚â§ RingHom.ker
          (Algebra.TensorProduct.lmul' (R := K) (S := L)).toRingHom := by
        rw [show IŒ¥ = Ideal.span {Œ¥} from rfl, Ideal.span_le, Set.singleton_subset_iff]
        exact hŒ¥
      exact hIŒ¥_subset_ker he_in_IŒ¥
    -- Step (iv): polynomial extraction. We have a non-trivial idempotent `e ‚àà L‚äóL`
    -- with `(e) = (Œ¥)` and `Œº(e) = 0`. We first derive the key consequences of
    -- `e` being idempotent and a generator of `(Œ¥)`.
    --
    -- (a) `1 - e` is also idempotent.
    have he_one_sub : IsIdempotentElem ((1 : L ‚äó[K] L) - e) := he_idem.one_sub
    -- (b) `e ¬∑ (1 - e) = 0` (the standard orthogonality of complementary idempotents).
    have he_orth : e * (1 - e) = 0 := he_idem.mul_one_sub_self
    -- (c) `Œ¥ ‚àà IŒ¥ = (e)`, so `Œ¥ = e ¬∑ s` for some `s ‚àà L‚äóL`.
    obtain ‚ü®s, hs‚ü© : ‚àÉ s : L ‚äó[K] L, Œ¥ = e * s := by
      have hŒ¥_in : Œ¥ ‚àà IŒ¥ := Ideal.mem_span_singleton_self Œ¥
      rw [he_span, Submodule.mem_span_singleton] at hŒ¥_in
      obtain ‚ü®s, hs‚ü© := hŒ¥_in
      exact ‚ü®s, by simpa [mul_comm] using hs.symm‚ü©
    -- (d) Hence `Œ¥ ¬∑ (1 - e) = 0`. Using commutativity of `L ‚äó L`:
    --     `Œ¥ ¬∑ (1 - e) = (e ¬∑ s) ¬∑ (1 - e) = (e ¬∑ (1 - e)) ¬∑ s = 0`.
    have hŒ¥_one_sub : Œ¥ * (1 - e) = 0 := by
      calc Œ¥ * (1 - e) = (e * s) * (1 - e) := by rw [hs]
        _ = (e * (1 - e)) * s := by ring
        _ = 0 * s := by rw [he_orth]
        _ = 0 := zero_mul _
    -- (e) Translating (d) via `Œ¥ = 1‚äóa - a‚äó1`:
    --     `(1‚äóa)¬∑(1-e) = (a‚äó1)¬∑(1-e)` in `L‚äóL`.
    have hkey : (1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a : L ‚äó[K] L) * (1 - e) = (a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 : L ‚äó[K] L) * (1 - e) := by
      have := hŒ¥_one_sub
      rw [hŒ¥_def, sub_mul] at this
      exact sub_eq_zero.mp this
    -- The remaining polynomial extraction. The key relation `hkey` says that, after
    -- multiplying by `(1 - e)`, the elements `1 ‚äó a` and `a ‚äó 1` agree in `L ‚äó_K L`.
    -- Concretely: in the ring `R‚ÇÇ := (1-e)¬∑(L‚äóL)` (with unit `1-e`), the image of
    -- `1 ‚äó a` equals the image of `a ‚äó 1`, where the latter is the image of `a` under
    -- the canonical section `L ‚Üí R‚ÇÇ`, `l ‚Ü¶ (1-e)¬∑(l‚äó1)` of the surjection
    -- `Œº‚ÇÇ : R‚ÇÇ ‚Üí L`. The K-algebra map `K[X] ‚Üí L‚äóL`, `X ‚Ü¶ 1‚äóa`, composed with the
    -- projection `L‚äóL ‚Üí R‚ÇÇ`, factors as `K[X] ‚Üí K ‚Üí R‚ÇÇ`, `X ‚Ü¶ a` (a scalar in the
    -- L-algebra structure of `R‚ÇÇ`). The kernel of this composite is therefore a
    -- non-trivial K[X]-ideal ‚Äî once we can detect when the composite K[X] ‚Üí L‚äóL ‚Üí R‚ÇÇ
    -- yields a polynomial relation that descends to one in K[X] annihilating `a` via
    -- `Œº‚ÇÇ : R‚ÇÇ ‚Üí L`. This descent is the residual technical step.
    --
    -- The detailed extraction (linking the relation `(1‚äóa - a‚äó1)¬∑(1-e) = 0` to a
    -- non-zero polynomial in `K[X]` annihilating `a` over `K`) follows the
    -- "K[X] ‚äó_K L ‚âÉ L[X] is a domain" argument from the blueprint
    -- (`lem:flat-tensor-over-field-imples-algebraic`).
    --
    -- We case-split on whether `Œ¥ = 0`. The case `Œ¥ = 0` (equivalent to `e = 0`
    -- by `IŒ¥ = (e)`) is closed completely via K-linear independence of
    -- `{1, a} ‚äó_K {1, a}` (when `a ‚àâ K`). The substantive case `Œ¥ ‚âÝ 0` requires
    -- the polyEquivTensor + domain-of-L[X] reasoning and is left as a typed
    -- `sorry` with full framework in scope.
    by_cases hŒ¥_eq_zero : Œ¥ = 0
    ¬∑ -- Case `Œ¥ = 0`: then `1 ‚äó a = a ‚äó 1` in `L ‚äó_K L`. By K-linear independence
      -- of the family `(i, j) ‚Ü¶ ![1, a] i ‚äó ![1, a] j` (which follows from
      -- `{1, a}` being K-linearly independent in `L` when `a ‚àâ algebraMap K L`,
      -- via `LinearIndependent.tmul_of_flat_left`), we deduce
      -- `a ‚àà Set.range (algebraMap K L)`, hence `a` is annihilated by
      -- `X - C k` (with `k ‚àà K` the preimage of `a`).
      have h_tmul_eq : (1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a : L ‚äó[K] L) = a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 := by
        have h_zero : (1 ‚äó‚Çú[K] a - a ‚äó‚Çú[K] 1 : L ‚äó[K] L) = 0 := by
          rw [‚Üê hŒ¥_def]; exact hŒ¥_eq_zero
        exact sub_eq_zero.mp h_zero
      -- Reduce: it suffices to find `k : K` with `algebraMap K L k = a`.
      suffices h_a_in_K : ‚àÉ k : K, algebraMap K L k = a by
        obtain ‚ü®k, hk‚ü© := h_a_in_K
        refine ‚ü®Polynomial.X - Polynomial.C k, Polynomial.X_sub_C_ne_zero k, ?_‚ü©
        simp [hk]
      -- Prove by contradiction; suppose `a ‚àâ range (algebraMap K L)`.
      by_contra h_not_in_K
      simp only [not_exists] at h_not_in_K
      -- Then `{1, a}` is K-linearly independent in `L` (`a ‚âÝ k ‚Ä¢ 1` for any `k`).
      have hli : LinearIndependent K (![(1 : L), a]) := by
        rw [LinearIndependent.pair_iff' (one_ne_zero (Œ± := L))]
        intro k hk
        apply h_not_in_K k
        rw [Algebra.smul_def, mul_one] at hk
        exact hk
      -- Tensor: the family `(i, j) ‚Ü¶ ![1, a] i ‚äó ![1, a] j` is also K-linearly
      -- independent (because `L` is K-flat: any field over a subfield is flat).
      have hli2 : LinearIndependent K
          (fun ij : Fin 2 √ó Fin 2 => (![(1 : L), a] ij.1) ‚äó‚Çú[K] (![(1 : L), a] ij.2)) :=
        hli.tmul_of_flat_left hli
      -- A linearly independent family is injective as a function on indices.
      have h_inj : Function.Injective (fun ij : Fin 2 √ó Fin 2 =>
          (![(1 : L), a] ij.1) ‚äó‚Çú[K] (![(1 : L), a] ij.2)) := hli2.injective
      -- The values at `(0, 1)` and `(1, 0)` are `1 ‚äó a` and `a ‚äó 1`, equal by
      -- `h_tmul_eq`. Injectivity forces `(0, 1) = (1, 0)` ‚Äî contradiction.
      have h01_eq_10 : ((0 : Fin 2), (1 : Fin 2)) = ((1 : Fin 2), (0 : Fin 2)) := by
        apply h_inj
        simp [h_tmul_eq]
      simp at h01_eq_10
    ¬∑ -- Case `Œ¥ ‚âÝ 0`: substantive case. The polyEquivTensor framework has been
      -- exhausted across iter-017/018/019 (five distinct dead-ends; see
      -- `task_results/.../FieldExtension.lean.md`). iter-020 pivots to the
      -- Stacks 092K route: prove `K ‚Üí K[a]` weakly √©tale (subalgebra descent),
      -- then `K[a] ‚äó_K K[a] ‚Üí K[a]` is flat, and in the transcendental case
      -- `K[a] = K[X]`, `K[a] ‚äó_K K[a] = K[X, Y]` is a domain, so the kernel
      -- `(X - Y)` of the multiplication map is principal in a domain hence
      -- (by being a flat ideal forced to be idempotent) either 0 or full ‚Äî
      -- both impossible.
      --
      -- Available scaffolding for the next iteration (all in scope here):
      -- * `Œ¥ : L ‚äó[K] L` (= `1 ‚äó a - a ‚äó 1`), with `hŒ¥_eq_zero : ¬¨Œ¥ = 0`.
      -- * `e : L ‚äó[K] L` idempotent with `Ideal.span {Œ¥} = Ideal.span {e}`
      --   (`he_idem`, `he_span`).
      -- * `hŒºe : Œº(e) = 0`.
      -- * `hkey : (1 ‚äó a) * (1 - e) = (a ‚äó 1) * (1 - e)` in `L ‚äó_K L`.
      -- * `hŒ¥_one_sub : Œ¥ * (1 - e) = 0`.
      -- * `e ‚âÝ 0` (immediate from `Œ¥ ‚âÝ 0` and `(Œ¥) = (e)`).
      --
      -- The residual obligation to close this branch is exactly the descent
      -- step: prove that the principal ideal `(Œ¥)_{Aa ‚äó_K Aa}` is idempotent
      -- in `Aa ‚äó_K Aa` (where `Aa := Algebra.adjoin K {a}`). The ambient ring
      -- `L ‚äó_K L` has `(Œ¥)` idempotent (via `hIŒ¥_idem`), but the principal
      -- ideal in the subring `Aa ‚äó_K Aa ‚Ü™ L ‚äó_K L` is generally smaller and
      -- its idempotency does not transfer directly without the descent.
      --
      -- See `Proetale/Mathlib/RingTheory/WeaklyEtale/Subalgebra.lean` (to be
      -- created) for the planned descent lemma, and the iter-020 plan
      -- (`.archon/iter/iter-020/objectives.md`) for the full strategy.
      exact isAlgebraic_of_isField_aux K L a hŒ¥_eq_zero
  refine ‚ü®?_, h_alg‚ü©
  -- Step 3: from algebraicity, derive separability element-by-element. Each `a : L`
  -- is algebraic, so lies in a finite subfield `K‚üÆa‚üØ = IntermediateField.adjoin K {a}`.
  -- We then need `FormallyUnramified K K‚üÆa‚üØ` (so that `iff_isSeparable` applies).
  -- The descent from `FormallyUnramified K L` to `FormallyUnramified K K‚üÆa‚üØ` along
  -- the (faithfully flat, since `K‚üÆa‚üØ` is a field and `L` is a nontrivial extension)
  -- inclusion `K‚üÆa‚üØ ‚Ü™ L` is captured below by a private helper, currently with a
  -- typed `sorry` for the K√§hler-differential descent argument.
  refine ‚ü®fun a => ?_‚ü©
  -- `a` is algebraic (from `h_alg`); package this as `IsIntegral K a`.
  have ha_int : IsIntegral K a := (h_alg.isAlgebraic a).isIntegral
  -- Build the finite intermediate field `K‚üÆa‚üØ`.
  let F : IntermediateField K L := IntermediateField.adjoin K ({a} : Set L)
  have hF_fin : FiniteDimensional K F :=
    IntermediateField.finiteDimensional_adjoin (S := ({a} : Set L)) (by simp [ha_int])
  -- `K‚üÆa‚üØ` is finite-dimensional over `K`, hence finite type, hence essentially of
  -- finite type.
  haveI : Module.Finite K F := hF_fin
  haveI : Algebra.FiniteType K F := Module.Finite.finiteType F
  haveI : Algebra.EssFiniteType K F := Algebra.EssFiniteType.of_finiteType K F
  -- Faithful flatness of `K ‚Üí F` (every nontrivial extension of a field is faithfully
  -- flat: `F` is `K`-free, hence flat; nontriviality gives the faithful condition).
  haveI : Module.FaithfullyFlat K F := inferInstance
  -- The hard step: descend `FormallyUnramified K L` along the inclusion `F ‚Ü™ L`.
  -- This uses faithful flatness of `F ‚Üí L` (every nontrivial field extension is
  -- faithfully flat) plus a K√§hler-differential argument on the cotangent sequence.
  -- See blueprint `lem:flat-tensor-over-field-imples-algebraic` end-of-proof.
  haveI hFU_F : Algebra.FormallyUnramified K F := by
    -- Strategy: `F ‚äó_K F` embeds into the reduced ring `L ‚äó_K L`, hence is reduced.
    -- It is also Artinian (finite-dim over the field `K`). A reduced Artinian ring is
    -- semisimple, so every ideal is generated by an idempotent, hence idempotent.
    -- Applied to the K√§hler differential ideal, this gives `Subsingleton Œ©[F/K]`,
    -- i.e. `FormallyUnramified K F`.
    have hinj_lin : Function.Injective
        (_root_.TensorProduct.map (R := K) F.val.toLinearMap F.val.toLinearMap) :=
      TensorProduct.map_injective_of_flat_flat _ _
        (F.val.injective : Function.Injective ‚áëF.val.toLinearMap)
        (F.val.injective : Function.Injective ‚áëF.val.toLinearMap)
    have hinj : Function.Injective
        ((Algebra.TensorProduct.map F.val F.val).toRingHom :
          ‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F ‚Üí+* L ‚äó[K] L) := hinj_lin
    have hReducedFF : IsReduced (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F) :=
      isReduced_of_injective _ hinj
    haveI : Module.Finite K (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F) := Module.Finite.tensorProduct K ‚Ü•F ‚Ü•F
    haveI : IsArtinianRing (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F) :=
      .of_finite K (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F)
    haveI : IsSemisimpleRing (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F) :=
      IsArtinianRing.isSemisimpleRing_of_isReduced (‚Ü•F ‚äó[K] ‚Ü•F)
    obtain ‚ü®e, he, hsp‚ü© := IsSemisimpleRing.ideal_eq_span_idempotent
      (KaehlerDifferential.ideal K ‚Ü•F)
    have hIdem : IsIdempotentElem (KaehlerDifferential.ideal K ‚Ü•F) := by
      show KaehlerDifferential.ideal K ‚Ü•F * KaehlerDifferential.ideal K ‚Ü•F =
          KaehlerDifferential.ideal K ‚Ü•F
      rw [hsp, Ideal.span_singleton_mul_span_singleton, he.eq]
    rw [Algebra.formallyUnramified_iff]
    exact (Ideal.cotangent_subsingleton_iff _).mpr hIdem
  -- Apply `iff_isSeparable` to conclude `Algebra.IsSeparable K F`.
  have hsep_F : Algebra.IsSeparable K F :=
    (Algebra.FormallyUnramified.iff_isSeparable K (L := F)).mp hFU_F
  -- Transfer from `a ‚àà F = K‚üÆa‚üØ` back to `a` itself in `L`.
  have ha_in_F : a ‚àà F := IntermediateField.subset_adjoin _ _ (by simp)
  have hsep_F_elem : IsSeparable K (‚ü®a, ha_in_F‚ü© : F) :=
    Algebra.IsSeparable.isSeparable' _
  rwa [IsSeparable, IntermediateField.minpoly_eq] at hsep_F_elem

end Algebra.WeaklyEtale
